  "prompt": "What are the lessons people most often learn too late in life?",
  "response": "Here are some common life lessons people often realize too late:\n\n1. Health-related lessons\n- Take care of your physical and mental health earlier\n- Exercise and eat well consistently\n- Don't take your health for granted\n- Get regular medical check-ups\n\n2. Relationship insights\n- Invest time in meaningful relationships\n- Tell people you love them\n- Spend more quality time with family and friends\n- Forgive and let go of grudges\n- Don't neglect relationships for work\n\n3. Personal growth\n- Pursue passions and dreams sooner\n- Take more risks\n- Learn continuously\n- Don't be afraid of failure\n- Step out of your comfort zone\n\n4. Financial wisdom\n- Start saving and investing early\n- Live below your means\n- Build multiple income streams\n- Understand financial literacy\n- Prioritize experiences over material possessions\n\n5. Time management\n- Time is the most valuable resource\n- Don't waste time on negative people\n- Balance work and personal life\n- Be present in the moment\n- Don't procrastinate\n\n6. Self-acceptance\n- Stop worrying about others' opinions\n- Be comfortable with yourself\n- Embrace your uniqueness\n- Practice self-love and self-compassion\n\n7. Career development\n- Continuous learning and skill development\n- Network and build professional relationships\n- Don't stay in unfulfilling jobs\n- Take calculated career risks\n\nThese lessons often come from personal experiences and reflections.",
